<item>
            <title>[PIG-4888] Line number off when reporting syntax error inside a macro</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4888</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;  1 /*&lt;br/&gt;
  2  * extra lines to offset the line number for the macro&lt;br/&gt;
  3  *&lt;br/&gt;
  4  *&lt;br/&gt;
  5  */&lt;br/&gt;
  6&lt;br/&gt;
  7&lt;br/&gt;
  8 define mymacro() returns void {&lt;br/&gt;
  9 A = load &apos;x&apos; as ( u:int, v:long, w:bytearray);&lt;br/&gt;
 10 B = limit A 100;&lt;br/&gt;
 11 C = &lt;font color=&quot;red&quot;&gt;filter_typo&lt;/font&gt; B by 2 &amp;gt; 1;&lt;br/&gt;
 12 D = load &apos;y&apos; as (d1, d2);&lt;br/&gt;
 13 E = join C by ( $0, $1 ), D by ( d1, d2 ) using &apos;replicated&apos; parallel 16;&lt;br/&gt;
 14 F = store E into &apos;output&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
 15 };&lt;br/&gt;
 16 mymacro();&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This fails with &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;2016-05-05 22:25:28,390 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;main&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ERROR org.apache.pig.tools.grunt.Grunt - ERROR 1200: &amp;lt;file test.pig, line 16&amp;gt; Failed to parse macro &apos;mymacro&apos;. Reason: &amp;lt;file /homes/knoguchi/test.pig, line 4, column 0&amp;gt;  Syntax error, unexpected symbol at or near &apos;C&apos;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;test.pig, line 4,&lt;/tt&gt; should have been line 11.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
